subject: Guet GUI
description:
As PP I want a visual interface so that I can use guet into a project more conveniently without typing commands.


Acceptance Test:
"guet GUI" should launch GUI from command-line

subject: Guet GUI - Add, Set, Get & Remove
description:
As a PP I want to add, set, get and remove programmers so that I can manage people in the repository.

Acceptance Criteria:

*   Interface must support adding new committers  
    Verify using “guet get all”
*   Interface must support removing existing committers  
    Verify using “guet get all”
*   Interface must display list of current/all committers
*   Interface must support setting committers for the current repository  
    Verify using “guet get current”

subject: Guet GUI - Initialization
description: As a PP I want to initialize guet into the project so that I can use all the guet related functionalities.

subject: Guet GUI - Remove Config
description: As a PP I want to remove guet configuration using interface so that I can remove guet config from the repository I am currently working on.

subject: PP Sessions Tracker
description:
As a PP I want to track specific PP sessions so that I can attribute multiple commits to a session.

Acceptance Criteria:


guet session start should start a new pair programming session.


While executing git commit, the timestamp should be added automatically in the comments if the session has started.


guet session end should end the pair programming session.

subject: Get team members from Taiga
description:
As a PP I want to get team members from Taiga so that I can set them as committers.

Acceptance Test:
Successfully display Taiga team members in the guet interface

subject: Build "ads" looking for team members to code with
description: As a PP I want to post ads so that I can inform all the team members that I am looking for one to code with.

subject: Get issues from GitHub project
description: As a PP I want to fetch issues from GitHub so that I can work on them.

subject: Indicate pairing strategy (driver/observer, senior/junior)
description:
As a PP I want to add a pairing strategy so that I can classify programmers in the commit.


Acceptance Test:
I should be able to designate any one committer as primary/driver.

subject: Alphebatize committers list
description:
As a PP I want to fetch committers list in alphabetical order so that I can find committers easily.

Acceptance Criteria:

\-guet get current

Driver in first position, followed by observers listed alphabetically

\-guet get all

All committers listed alphabetically

subject: Warn a user when set committers and commit committers differ
description: As a PP I want to warn the user when set committers and commit committers are different so that I can avoid errors.

subject: guet command not found (Windows)
description:
As a PP I want to be able to use guet on windows machines so that I do not have to use any workarounds.


Acceptance Test:
guet init
guet add
guet set 
guet get
guet remove
guet yeet


Following commands should work in windows command-line.

subject: Post add/remove notifications to Slack
description:
As a programmer, I want to see guet updates on slack, so that it's convenient to me.

Acceptance criterion:
Add/remove guet update shown as slack notifications.

subject: Duplicate users can be added using guet set
description:
As a user
I want the program to not set the same committer twice if I mention it multiple times accidentally
So that it does not confusion in the commit messages

subject: Save team members from taiga as committers
description:
As a programmer, I want to pull my team members from taiga and add them as committers so that I do not have to add them manually

Acceptance Criteria:

“guet taiga members” should prompt the user after displaying the team members if they would like to add them as committers

“guet get all” should verify that the members have been added

subject: Aggregate contributions from each committer
description:
As a programmer, I want to see contributions from all the other committers, so that I am up to date with my team.

Acceptance criterion:
Committers contributions are shown accurately like in git log.

subject: Format github issues for better readability
description:
As a programmer, I want to be able to see the issues in a readable format so there is no ambiguity.

Acceptance Criteria:

“guet github issues” should print the issues in following format:

Issue# : Issue Title

Description

…

subject: PP session tracking
description:
Duplicate of #11

As a PP I want to track specific PP sessions so that I can attribute multiple commits to a session.

Acceptance Criteria:

guet session start should start a new pair programming session.

While executing git commit, the timestamp should be added automatically in the comments if the session has started.

guet session end should end the pair programming session.

subject: Duplicate committers in GUI - Add button
description: As a developer, I want to know if I added an initial already existing in the GUI, so that I can change it then and there.

subject: GUI returns error or success messages for various commands
description:
As a programmer, I want to know if my command was a success or failure, so that I can know what to do next.

Acceptance criteron:
Success or failure messages pop up in the GUI

subject: GUI should show if a PP already exists in the record when added again
description:
As a programmer, I want to know if the programmer already exists in the record in GUI itself, so that I can proceed accordingly.

Acceptance criterion:
GUI returns a message if an identical PP is added again.
